<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Allenisms Were a Hoot
</HL>
<DATE>
08/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<LP>
   I'm surprised that Frederick C. Klein, when writing about
baseball announcer Mel Allen (Leisure &amp; Arts, June 29), chose
to recall "Ballantine blast" from the immediate post-World
War II period instead of a more quintessential Allenism, such
as, "Foul, by the width of a White Owl cigar]"
   L. Brooks Hughes
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Marshall, Mich.
</TEXT>
